Sec. 161.034. PUBLIC MEETINGS. (a) The commission is subject
to the open meetings law, Chapter 551, Government Code.
(b) The commission shall develop and implement policies that
provide the public with a reasonable opportunity to appear before the
commission and to speak on any issue under the jurisdiction of the
commission.
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 879 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

(c) Each meeting of the commission must be held in a location
that provides adequate access to members of the public.
(d) The commission shall post audio archives of its meetings on
the commission's Internet website.
Added by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 836, Sec. 12, eff. Sept. 1, 1989.
Amended by Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 554, Sec. 14, eff. Sept. 1,
1995.
Amended by:
Acts 2007, 80th Leg., R.S., Ch. 1242 (H.B. 2543), Sec. 9(a), eff.
September 1, 2007.

